    {
      "id": 4,
      "page": null,
      "type": "Title",
      "text": "Section 1 – Executive Summary",
      "section_path": "Section 1 – Executive Summary"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "page": null,
      "type": "Title",
      "text": "1.1 Overview",
      "section_path": "1.1 Overview"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Full‑year FY2024 net revenue grew 7.2% year‑over‑year to USD 3.45B, driven primarily by same‑store sales growth in the Core Retail segment and continued expansion of our Marketplace offering.",
      "section_path": "1.1 Overview"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Q4 FY2024 operating margin was 9.8%, up 80 bps versus Q4 FY2023, reflecting improved inventory discipline and lower freight costs, partially offset by higher wage investments.",
      "section_path": "1.1 Overview"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Free cash flow for FY2024 was USD 245M, an increase of USD 60M versus the prior year, supporting continued store remodels and technology investments.",
      "section_path": "1.1 Overview"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Key risks heading into FY2025 include softer discretionary spending, ongoing wage inflation, and continued pressure on delivery costs for same‑day fulfillment.",
      "section_path": "1.1 Overview"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "page": null,
      "type": "Title",
      "text": "1.2 Key highlights",
      "section_path": "1.2 Key highlights"
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Core Retail comp sales were +5.1% for the full year, with strength in Essentials and Beauty offsetting softness in Home and Electronics.",
      "section_path": "1.2 Key highlights"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Marketplace gross merchandise value (GMV) grew 32% year‑over‑year, now representing 11% of consolidated revenue.",
      "section_path": "1.2 Key highlights"
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Digital sales grew 14% year‑over‑year and now account for 24% of total revenue; same‑day services (pickup and delivery) represent 62% of digital orders.",
      "section_path": "1.2 Key highlights"
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "We ended the year with net debt / EBITDA of 1.9x, within the Board’s target range of 1.5x– 2.0x and comfortably inside our covenant threshold of 3.5x.",
      "section_path": "1.2 Key highlights"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "page": null,
      "type": "Title",
      "text": "1.3 Key watchpoints",
      "section_path": "1.3 Key watchpoints"
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Gross margin improved by 60 bps year‑over‑year, but we are seeing pressure from promotional intensity in Q1 FY2025 to clear seasonal inventory.",
      "section_path": "1.3 Key watchpoints"
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Store labor hours per transaction increased 3%, driven by higher service levels and training for new associates; productivity initiatives are planned for H1.",
      "section_path": "1.3 Key watchpoints"
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "page": null,
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Marketplace returns and refund rates are trending above plan in select categories; FP&A and Operations are working on a root cause analysis and revised fee structure.",
      "section_path": "1.3 Key watchpoints"
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "page": null,
      "type": "UncategorizedText",
      "text": "---",
      "section_path": "1.3 Key watchpoints"
    },
    {
